Game.Name: Sightwaves
Game.Description:
This was our submission for Global Game Jam 2017, the first game jam that John, Will and Dan ever went to, before Tim joined the team, at the Jam Site of the University of Lincoln.
The Theme for this year was 'Waves', so we came came up with the idea of the player not being able to see through normal means, instead seeing the world through sound. So as a player you need to make noise in order to see the world and make your way through abandoned structures and puzzles to find your way back home.

Game.Name: The Lone Astronaut
Game.Description:
This was our submission for the Global Game Jam 2018, with Tim Weightman officially joining the team and Luke Garside also joining for a few game jams.
The theme for this year was 'Transmission' so the game we developed was inspired by "The Martian" and had the player trapped on the planet Mars needing to complete many different puzzles in order to escape back home to earth.

Game.Name: Time To Kill
Game.Description:
With a theme of 'Time', we made 'Time To Kill'. The team was John Weightman, Tim Weightman, Will Dixon, Daniel Dennis and Luke Garside. This was for CanJam 2018 at the University of Lincoln.
Navigate an abandoned lab, sneaking around a ruthless murdering robot and collecting parts of an EMP, putting an end to his rampage. Uncover the mystery behind what happened to the staff, and how they met their gruesome ends.
